I just looked in on
Caldwell's burn patient, 3311.

35:06.640 --> 35:10.080
He's haemorrhaging under the
skin graft. Have you seen Bobby?

35:10.080 --> 35:12.880
You know, he's not answering
his beeper. Should we page him?

35:12.880 --> 35:16.880
          With pleasure.

35:18.560 --> 35:20.240
(MOANS) Oh, Bobby!

35:20.240 --> 35:22.760
(MOANS) Oh, Bobby!
(TANNOY) Dr Robert Caldwell,
third floor nurses' station.

35:22.760 --> 35:25.040
Bobby?!

35:25.040 --> 35:27.600
Gotta go.  Just like that?

35:27.600 --> 35:30.600
I'm being paged!  So?!

35:30.600 --> 35:33.520
I told you - I'm on call.

35:33.520 --> 35:37.520
Oh...

35:39.920 --> 35:41.960
Somebody took our clothes!

35:41.960 --> 35:44.520
Multiple superficial pellet
wounds to the right shoulder!

35:44.520 --> 35:47.280
         Extremity intact.

35:47.280 --> 35:50.120
There's another one coming
in behind us! Head trauma.

35:50.120 --> 35:52.240
The scum better be dead or
I'll finish the job myself.

35:52.240 --> 35:53.720
Knock it off.

35:53.720 --> 35:55.360
      BP's 126/80, pulse 96.

35:55.360 --> 35:57.920
OK, start a line.
Crid type and cross for two.

35:57.920 --> 36:01.760
Helen, I need ringers.
Will you take this guy?

36:01.760 --> 36:04.840
A real mess! Severe crushing
to the left side of the skull.

36:04.840 --> 36:07.440
Obvious open cranium with
exposed brain tissue.

36:07.440 --> 36:09.520
Don't intubate.

36:09.520 --> 36:12.320
Ask the cops about next of kin.

36:12.320 --> 36:16.320
Ask the cops about next of kin.
    He doesn't have any family.

36:21.200 --> 36:23.240
We've been searching
high and low for you!

36:23.240 --> 36:27.240
Ehrlich, you are a dead man!
I want my scrubs now!

36:30.040 --> 36:33.160
Oh, you know, you don't look
half bad without your clothes on.

36:33.160 --> 36:36.000
Oh, but I'd wax my back,
if I were you.

36:36.000 --> 36:39.240
Your, er, fly boy's got some
bleeding at the surgical site.

36:39.240 --> 36:42.840
Nothing serious,
but I didn't want to damage
 the graft by applying pressure.

36:42.840 --> 36:44.360
Aren't you gonna ask him?  Huh?

36:44.360 --> 36:46.360
Aren't you gonna ask him?  Huh?
Oh, yeah!

36:46.360 --> 36:49.160
Lucy and I figured out
about the rubber bands, but...

36:49.160 --> 36:53.160
what are you gonna do with
the bowling ball?! Huh?!

36:53.680 --> 36:56.120
 "Your body needs food for energy.

36:56.120 --> 36:59.160
"But if you eat more
than you expend in energy,

36:59.160 --> 37:03.160
"your body stores
the surplus in the form of fat.

37:03.400 --> 37:06.400
"When the amount of fat
becomes excessive or unsightly,

37:06.400 --> 37:10.200
    "you are considered obese."

37:10.200 --> 37:14.200
Ugh!

37:15.080 --> 37:18.560
(PANTS) You know,
my father used to call me "Squirt".

37:18.560 --> 37:22.000
One day, he came to me and he said,
"Ever been to Hershey, Squirt?"

37:22.000 --> 37:24.800
Best vacation I ever had!

37:24.800 --> 37:28.800
The whole town smelt like chocolate.
My mom and dad used to take me
   on a  lot of themed vacations.

37:30.000 --> 37:32.000
Wisconsin for the cheese.

37:32.000 --> 37:33.640
Vermont for the maple syrup.

37:33.640 --> 37:35.400
Idaho for the potatoes.

37:35.400 --> 37:38.360
But the best vacation I ever had -
Hershey, Pennsylvania.

37:38.360 --> 37:40.840
      OK, all right. 20 more.

37:40.840 --> 37:43.080
Everybody there used to make
chocolate, with and without nuts.

37:43.080 --> 37:44.560
Everybody there used to make
chocolate, with and without nuts.
           Start rowing.

37:44.560 --> 37:47.960
I can't do this any more!
I'm exhausted, I'm drained!

37:47.960 --> 37:49.720
            You're fat!

37:49.720 --> 37:52.480
"Fat" is a relative term.
Compared to some people, I'm svelte!

37:52.480 --> 37:56.480
Humpy dumpy, maybe!
Now, start rowing!

37:58.280 --> 38:02.280
              One...

38:04.840 --> 38:08.840
              Helen?

38:15.280 --> 38:19.280
I heard about Nick Meose, um...
I'm very sorry I didn't listen.

38:21.400 --> 38:25.400
I'm sitting here trying to remember
why I wanted to get  transferred
          to emergency.

38:27.440 --> 38:31.440
A teenage boy...and a friend of
 mine's son  die and I stand by?!

38:33.520 --> 38:34.920
    You're a good nurse, Helen.

38:34.920 --> 38:36.760
    You're a good nurse, Helen.
Oh, I know that!

38:36.760 --> 38:40.760
Why they hell did I ever want to
become one in the first place?!

38:40.920 --> 38:44.920
I'm going to see the head of
nursing, get transferred upstairs.

38:47.160 --> 38:49.480
Let someone else cry for Nick Meose.

38:49.480 --> 38:53.480
I don't have the heart any more.

38:55.600 --> 38:59.600
THUNDER

38:59.840 --> 39:03.520
How many people are you
expecting at the funeral?

39:03.520 --> 39:06.120
I don't know, Mark.

39:06.120 --> 39:10.040
I bet they'll be dropping
back here for calling hours.

39:10.040 --> 39:13.880
Making a mess of the downstairs.
The caterers will clear it all up.

39:13.880 --> 39:16.880
Well, they better.
I've seen what they charge.

39:16.880 --> 39:20.880
Why do we keep using those
clods anyway?

39:22.680 --> 39:26.600
      Had to rain, didn't it?

39:26.600 --> 39:30.600
I never could get
this damn thing straight!

39:30.720 --> 39:34.720
Zip me up, please.

39:39.360 --> 39:41.080
      You know, it's lucky...

39:41.080 --> 39:43.240
I called the limousine
about directions.

39:43.240 --> 39:47.240
That driver thought
we lived in Newton.

39:49.280 --> 39:53.280
   He should be here any minute.

39:54.480 --> 39:58.480
I forgot to ask Reverend Ives
if he'd be reading from the King
James version.

39:59.120 --> 40:00.240
Damn it, Mark!

40:00.240 --> 40:03.800
We're saying goodbye
    to Stephen this afternoon

40:03.800 --> 40:05.960
and all you think about
       is trivial things!

40:05.960 --> 40:08.160
I want to make sure
the protocol is right.

40:08.160 --> 40:11.200
We are burying our son!

40:11.200 --> 40:13.000
       It's just a ceremony.

40:13.000 --> 40:15.480
       It's just a ceremony.
No, it's not!

40:15.480 --> 40:18.120
We're putting Stephen in a hole
in the ground and covering him up!

40:18.120 --> 40:19.920
     Don't be macabre, Ellen!

40:19.920 --> 40:23.360
Well, it is macabre, Mark!
Only you won't face it.

40:23.360 --> 40:26.480
And I don't how to.

40:26.480 --> 40:28.120
Well, the Valium's not gonna help.

40:28.120 --> 40:29.440
You have to have a clear
head to deal with this!

40:29.440 --> 40:32.800
I don't want to remember today,
I just want to get through it!

40:32.800 --> 40:34.680
   That's a bad attitude, Ellen.

40:34.680 --> 40:38.680
Well, I need the crutch,
because you've been no help to me
        at all in this!

40:48.280 --> 40:52.200
               Yeah?

40:52.200 --> 40:54.720
Look what Tommy gave me.

40:54.720 --> 40:55.840
               Oh...

40:55.840 --> 40:59.840
He used to draw with only one colour.
Now he's using the rest of the
crayons, too. That's great.

41:00.960 --> 41:04.960
He's much happier now.  Taking him
out of family care was a good move.

41:08.080 --> 41:11.080
Listen, Donald, I'm sorry
about what I said downstairs.

41:11.080 --> 41:13.080
   No, you're not. You meant it.

41:13.080 --> 41:17.080
Yeah, but I feel bad.
You didn't deserve a lecture.

41:17.800 --> 41:20.640
You know, you remind
me of Maureen sometimes?

41:20.640 --> 41:22.360
You know, you remind
me of Maureen sometimes?
Because she was opinionated?

41:22.360 --> 41:26.120
Yeah. How long are you
gonna stay with us?

41:26.120 --> 41:30.120
It'll take a couple of weeks
to help you get settled,
help you interview housekeepers.

41:31.200 --> 41:32.000
 Well, I wish it could be longer.

41:32.000 --> 41:33.600
 Well, I wish it could be longer.
Thanks.

41:33.600 --> 41:36.400
Mommy!

41:36.400 --> 41:40.400
Weird.

42:10.280 --> 42:13.320
              Ellen?

42:13.320 --> 42:17.320
             Let's go.

42:17.320 --> 42:20.720
I can't, Mark.

42:20.720 --> 42:24.720
        People are waiting.

42:25.200 --> 42:29.200
I can't go up there.

42:43.600 --> 42:46.880
        It'll be OK, Ellen.

42:46.880 --> 42:49.760
     We'll get through this...

42:49.760 --> 42:53.760
            ..together.

